-- MOVES-Astrid Manroth joins Deutsche AWM from World Bank
-- 
-- Mon Sep 22, 2014 08:47AM EDT
-- None



Sept 22 (Reuters) - Investment manager Deutsche Asset & Wealth Management (Deutsche AWM) said it appointed Astrid Manroth as managing director and head of environment and social capital within the sustainable investments platform of alternatives and real assets in Europe.

Manroth will manage the expansion of the environmental and social capital business based in Frankfurt and the development finance business based in Luxembourg, Deutsche AWM said in a statement.